verbose_text: In the developing fetal rat testis, partial inhibition of Coup-tf2 by phthalates causes expansion of Leydig cells and an increase in the intratesticular testosterone concentration, consistent with Coup-tf2 being a factor repressing fetal androgenization.
evidence: Coup-tf2 by phthalates causes expansion of Leydig cells and an increase in the intratesticular testosterone
